    "biography": "<p>Lurking in the swampy depths of the wilderness, the Nekrozon looms as a formidable beast, its massive buffalo-like body crowned with a long neck, a boar’s fierce head, and a lengthy tail. Known in ancient tales as a 'catoblepas,' a name now lost to time, it haunts these boggy realms with a deadly presence.</p><p>It strikes with the bony tip of its tail, inflicting [[/r 1d6 #Tail damage]] and carrying a 50% chance to knock down and stun its target for [[/r 1d6 #Rounds stunned]] (save vs. paralysis to resist). Its gaze, a 60-foot magical death ray, activates only if it lifts its head—a 1-in-4 chance each round—killing instantly unless a save vs. death ray prevails. Accidental eye contact on complete surprise (1 on 1d6) brings unavoidable death.</p><p>Impervious to energy drains, death rays, and instant-death effects except through raw damage, the Nekrozon roams alone or in small groups of [[/r 1d3 #Nekrozons in lair]], guarding modest treasures amidst the mire.</p><p><strong>Terrain:</strong> Swamps</p>",
